observations.recommendation:
We have recommended the following:
 The Budget Officer and Accountant justify the non-maintenance of the required registries, failure to duly accomplish the required obligation request as well as the non-submission of SAAOB;
 The Budget Officer coordinate accordingly with the Accountant in the preparation and submission of the SCBAA the soonest possible time so as to allow the audit team to have ample time to verify its validity;
 The Budget Officer and different department heads strictly adhere to the budgetary and disbursement process; and
 Henceforth, management familiarize themselves and ensure strict compliance with the different budgetary requirements.

In view of the foregoing, we have recommended that:
 Management create an Inventory Committee that will perform the conduct of complete annual physical count of PPE in accordance with Section 124 of the Manual on the NGAS for LGUs, Vol. 1. A representative of the Auditor be invited to witness the inventory taking for this purpose;
 the Property and Accounting Units maintain complete and accurate PPELC for each category of PPE pursuant to Section 114 on the NGAS Manual for LGUs in order to promote effective monitoring and controls over PPE;
 a reconciliation of the Property and Accounting records be done after the conduct of physical count; and
 the Inventory Committee submit the Physical Inventory Reports to the Property Officer and COA Office for verification and reconciliation of the result of the physical inventory with the complete Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards and the Property Cards maintained by the Property and Accounting Units;  ARE/PAR be maintained and renewed every three years in accordance with the Instructions on the use of ARE/PAR;  the Property and Accounting Units comply with the prescribed procedures in COA Circular No. 89-296 on the disposal of unserviceable PPE, if any; and  Management transfer to the Department of Education the cost of the school building through a Journal Entry Voucher to be drawn by the Municipal Accountant and copy furnished the Accountant of DepEd.

We have recommended the following:
 That the agency integrate in its budgeting an amount equal to 5% of the total appropriation for PPAs that address gender issues;
 That a Gender and Development Plan be prepared containing the specific projects and activities addressing gender and development and equity for women and the utilization should be in accordance with the GAD Plan;
 Ensure that Obligation Requests (OBRs) be duly accomplished and required registries of allotment and obligations are maintained; and
 Ensure that Accomplishment Reports contain the actual accomplishment vis-à-vis targets as well as the amounts utilized and a list of expenditures that are related with the utilization of the said fund.

In view of the foregoing, we have recommended that:
• Management create an Inventory Committee that will perform the conduct of complete annual physical count of PPE in accordance with Section 124 of the Manual on the NGAS for LGUs, Vol. 1. A representative of the Auditor be invited to witness the inventory taking for this purpose;
• the Property and Accounting Units maintain complete and accurate PPELC for each category of PPE pursuant to Section 114 on the NGAS Manual for LGUs in order to promote effective monitoring and controls over PPE;
• a reconciliation of the Property and Accounting records be done after the conduct of physical count;
• the Inventory Committee submit the Physical Inventory Reports to the Property Officer and COA Office for verification and reconciliation of the result of the physical inventory with the complete Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards and the Property Cards maintained by the Property and Accounting Units;
• ARE/PAR be maintained and renewed every three years in accordance with the Instructions on the use of ARE/PAR;
• the Property and Accounting Units comply with the prescribed procedures in COA Circular No. 89-296 on the disposal of unserviceable PPE, if any; and
• Management transfer to the Department of Education the cost of the school building through a Journal Entry Voucher to be drawn by the Municipal Accountant and copy furnished the Accountant of DepEd.

In view of the foregoing, we have recommended that:
Management create an Inventory Committee that will perform the conduct of complete annual physical count of PPE in accordance with Section 124 of the Manual on the NGAS for LGUs, Vol. 1.  A representative of the Auditor be invited to witness the inventory taking for this purpose;
the Property and Accounting Units maintain complete and accurate PPELC for each category of PPE pursuant to Section 114 on the NGAS Manual for LGUs in order to promote effective monitoring and controls over PPE;
