the Inventory Committee submit the Physical Inventory Reports to the Property Officer and COA Office for verification and reconciliation of the result of the physical inventory with the complete Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards and the Property Cards maintained by the Property and Accounting Units;
ARE/PAR be maintained and renewed every three years in accordance with the Instructions on the use of ARE/PAR;
the Property and Accounting Units comply with the prescribed procedures in COA Circular No. 89-296 on the disposal of unserviceable PPE, if any; and
Management transfer to the Department of Education the cost of the school building through a Journal Entry Voucher to be drawn by the Municipal Accountant and copy furnished the Accountant of DepEd.

We have recommended the following:

The Municipal Mayor, Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer exert more effort to enforce collection or submission of liquidation documents by the employees with outstanding cash advances by withholding their salaries;
Municipal Employees should not be granted cash advance except for travelling expenses; 
Payments exceeding ₱15,000.00 should be paid through check
